@NODE "HIST" "History"

@{b}Changes@{ub}:

v2.2: When updating a Catalog Description (.cd), the strMin
      and strMax values were not preserved. - Fixed.

      When scanning a source script for strings to translate,
      any function name ending by 'tls' was misinterpreted
      as the tls() function to check. - Fixed.

      When using either MakeRexCat, MakeCD or MakeCT
      (AmigaDos scripts), the last selected source file is
      now remembered for a time (-> ENV:RexCatLastSrc).

      RexCat catalogs now have a $VER string.

v2.1: Added support for IFF catalogs (using locale.library).
      MakeRexCat.rexx has 2 new commands (MAKECD and MAKECT)
      which create a Catalog Description file and a Catalog
      Translation file.  (You still need a catalog compiler
      to build the IFF catalog.)

      When reading the .catalog file, a test to validate
      entries was wrong and caused some specially formatted
      strings to be ignored. - Fixed.

v2.0: First Aminet release.
      RexCat is a replacement for the maketls tool which
      was not released as standalone but included with
      some other ARexx applications.

@ENDNODE

